\title: Expected Value

\sec: Definition

For a random variable $X$, the \jarg <expected value(|s)> [expected value] $\mathbb E X$ is defined to be its average value over all possible events; that is,

\katex: \mathbb E X := \sum_{\omega \in \Omega} P(\omega) X(\omega)


\sec: Properties

- The expected value is a linear operator with respect to random variables; that is, we have:
    1. $\mathbb E(X + Y) = \mathbb EX + \mathbb EY$
    2. $\mathbb E(cX) = c\cdot \mathbb EX$
